info.description:
hybris-cis-mock-subscription-web

Parent pom providing dependency and plugin management for applications built with Maven
info.title: hybris-cis-mock-subscription-web

tags.name: AccountController
tags.description: Controller for create, read and update operations on subscription accounts.

tags.name: BillingActivityDetailsController
tags.description: Controller for reading billing activity details.

tags.name: ExternalServicesController
tags.description: Controller which provides utility endpoints related to third party services.

tags.name: PaymentMethodController
tags.description: Controller for updating of payment methods.

tags.name: SubscriptionController
tags.description:
Controller for creating, updating, changing subscription state, replacing payment method,
cancelling and upgrading subscriptions and getting billing activity list
for a subscription.

tags.name: TransactionsController
tags.description: Controller for processing one time transactions.

tags.name: WebSessionController
tags.description: Controller which manages web sessions with third party billing providers.

action.description: Returns a String representing the change action to be performed. Potential values depend on the particular implementation (e.g. activate, deactivate,...).

Returns a boolean flag indicating whether the change should be propagated to subscriptions using the payment
method.

json_CisSubscriptionCancelSubscriptionRe.title: CisSubscriptionCancelSubscriptionRequest

cancelationMode.description:
Returns a String representing the cancellation mode to use. The cancellation mode determines how to handle
refunding of pre-paid usage or charging of outstanding payments. Possible values are implementation specific.

force.description:
Returns a boolean flag indicating whether the subscription should be cancelled immediately (i.e. even within a
defined commitment period).

post.description:
Creates new account.

Example URL: POST
https://localhost:8443/hybris-cis-mock-subscription-web/sub/cisSubscriptionMock/accounts

get.description:
Returns an already existing account.

Example URL: GET
https://localhost:8443/hybris-cis-mock-subscription-web/sub/cisSubscriptionMock/accounts/1234567890

parameters.name: accountId
parameters.description: id of the account to get

put.description:
Updates an already existing account.

Example URL: PUT
https://localhost:8443/hybris-cis-mock-subscription-web/sub/cisSubscriptionMock/accounts/1234567890

parameters.name: accountId
parameters.description: id of the account to update

get.description:
Returns specific billing activity detail.

Example URL: GET
https://localhost:8443/hybris-cis-mock-subscription-web/sub/cisSubscriptionMock
/billingActivityDetails/535355500

200.description: the response with billing activity detail

head.description:
Returns Hosted Payment Framework (HPF) URL.

Example URL: HEAD
https://localhost:8443/hybris-cis-mock-subscription-web/sub/cisSubscriptionMock/hpfurl

put.description:
Updates an existing payment method.

Example URL: PUT
https://localhost:8443/hybris-cis-mock-subscription-web/sub/cisSubscriptionMock
/paymentmethods/25562724555

parameters.name: paymentMethodId
parameters.description: the id of payment method to update

204.description: the response with the updated payment method

head.summary: Tests connection with third party service using current credentials and properties.
head.description:
Tests connection with third party service using current credentials and properties.

Example URL: HEAD
https://localhost:8443/hybris-cis-mock-subscription-web/sub/cisSubscriptionMock/ping

200.description: the result of testing the connection

post.description:
Creates a new subscription.

Example URL: POST
https://localhost:8443/hybris-cis-mock-subscription-web/sub/cisSubscriptionMock/subscriptions

201.description: the response with new subscription data

put.description:
Updates an already existing subscription.

Example URL: PUT
https://localhost:8443/hybris-cis-mock-subscription-web/sub/cisSubscriptionMock/subscriptions/9997000011804610

204.description: the response with updated subscription data

get.summary: Returns the billing activities for the given subscription optionally filtered by date.
get.description:
Returns the billing activities for the given subscription optionally filtered by date.

Example URL: GET
https://localhost:8443/hybris-cis-mock-subscription-web/sub/cisSubscriptionMock/subscriptions/9997000011804610
/billingActivities

parameters.name: fromTimestamp
parameters.description: timestamp containing the 'from' date to filter by

parameters.name: toTimestamp
parameters.description: timestamp containing the 'to' date to filter by

200.description: the response with the list of billing activities

put.description:
Cancels the already existing subscription.

Example URL: PUT
https://localhost:8443/hybris-cis-mock-subscription-web/sub/cisSubscriptionMock/subscriptions/9997000011804610
/cancel?effectiveFrom=NOW

parameters.name: effectiveFrom
parameters.description: when the cancellation should take effect

204.description: the response with updated subscription data

put.summary: Changes the state of an already existing subscription.
put.description:
Changes the state of an already existing subscription.

Example URL: PUT
https://localhost:8443/hybris-cis-mock-subscription-web/sub/cisSubscriptionMock/subscriptions/9997000011804610
/changeState

204.description: the response with updated subscription data

put.summary: Replaces the payment method of an already existing subscription.
put.description:
Replaces the payment method of an already existing subscription.

Example URL: PUT
https://localhost:8443/hybris-cis-mock-subscription-web/sub/cisSubscriptionMock/subscriptions/9997000011804610
/replacePaymentMethod?merchantPaymentMethodId=9997000012761537&effectiveFrom=NOW

parameters.name: effectiveFrom
parameters.description: when the replacement should take effect

parameters.name: merchantPaymentMethodId
parameters.description: the id of the new payment method for subscription

204.description: the response with updated subscription data

put.description:
Upgrades the already existing subscription.

Example URL: PUT
https://localhost:8443/hybris-cis-mock-subscription-web/sub/cisSubscriptionMock/subscriptions/9997000011804610
/upgrade

204.description: the response with the upgrade result

post.summary: Authorizes and captures a one time transaction.
post.description:
Authorizes and captures a one time transaction.

Example URL: POST
https://localhost:8443/hybris-cis-mock-subscription-web/sub/cisSubscriptionMock/transactions

parameters.name: body
parameters.description: the request for processing a one time transaction

201.description: the subscription transaction result with details of the AuthCapture

put.summary: Passes customer usage for a subscription.
put.description:
Passes customer usage for a subscription.

Example URL: PUT
https://localhost:8443/hybris-cis-mock-subscription-web/sub/cisSubscriptionMock/usages

204.description: the response with the customer usage result

post.summary: Initializes a session with the third party billing provider.
post.description:
Initializes a session with the third party billing provider.

Example URL: POST
https://localhost:8443/hybris-cis-mock-subscription-web/sub/cisSubscriptionMock/websessions

201.description: the subscription transaction result with the transaction details

put.summary: Finalizes an already initialized session with the third party billing provider.
put.description: Finalizes an already initialized session with the third party billing provider.

parameters.name: websessionId
parameters.description: the id of the initialized web session

204.description: the subscription transaction result with details of the finalization
